<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="How_to_create_a_new_Bookshelf_page">How to create a new Bookshelf page</span></h2>
<p>Everybody can create new pages. 
</p>
<ol><li> Go to the <a href="/wiki/Special:Search" title="Special:Search">Search Page</a>.</li>
<li> Enter the page name into the search box.  Make sure the page name is spelled right and ends with a space and "(Bookshelf)", eg. "Novels (Bookshelf)".</li>
<li> Click "Search".</li>
<li> Check if the bookshelf exists already, else click on "create the page" link.</li>
<li> To make a page member of Category:Bookshelf just add <code>[[Category:Bookshelf]]</code> to the page (preferably the last line at the bottom). </li>
<li> Save the page.</li></ol>
<p>To make your life easier you should use following templates: 
</p><p><a href="/wiki/User:Marcello" title="User:Marcello">Marcello</a> 13:54, 12 December 2006 (EST)
</p>
