<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="email_for_non-volunteers">email for non-volunteers</span></h2>
<p>Is it possible to have an email (list) address at PG so Bookshelf users can easily send a message via link on the Bookshelf pages?
That would allow to get hints about books to add when the users are too lazy or shy to register and do it themselves.
Spam may become a problem, but then we can simply delete the list and declare the experiment closed. <a href="/wiki/User:Robert_Marquardt" title="User:Robert Marquardt">Robert Marquardt</a> 13:34, 19 January 2007 (EST)
</p>
<dl><dd>I'm thinking it might be easier (and better) to allow anonymous users to post only on "user talk" namespace?  That way we can have links to our user talk pages and we can be notified by e-mail if we choose but, it will also avoid spam and keep it on site (and easier for those making requests).  I think it's also built into Media Wiki that you can do that. <a href="/wiki/User:Grenavitar" title="User:Grenavitar">Grenavitar</a> 23:21, 19 January 2007 (EST)</dd></dl>
<p>This would allow the users to communicate between themselves. I would prefer an easy one way communication only. See the PG email lists. Users only interested in sending requests can do it easily. Those who want to read the messages from the other users will have to subscribe to the list and is hooked&#160;:-) <a href="/wiki/User:Robert_Marquardt" title="User:Robert Marquardt">Robert Marquardt</a> 01:34, 20 January 2007 (EST)
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Historical_Fiction">Historical Fiction</span></h2>
<p>There's a book in PG that's basically a catalogue of historical fiction, nicely sorted by subject period: the DP wiki has the list <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.pgdp.net/wiki/Historical_fiction">[1]</a> annotated with details of which books are in progress and which are in PG. It has a cutoff of publication date around 1900, and the book status has not been updated much lately, but it'd be a good starter for a bookshelf page. (ideally we need to keep the DP and PG wiki listings in sync somehow...) <a href="/wiki/User:Malcolm_Farmer" title="User:Malcolm Farmer">Malcolm Farmer</a> 04:56, 20 January 2007 (EST)
</p>
